-- Singapore Formula One Visitors Spent S$560 Million Since 2008
-- B y   S h a r o n   C h e n
-- 2012-09-12T10:44:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-12/singapore-formula-one-visitors-spent-s-560-million-since-2008.html
International visitors to the
 Singapore  Formula One Grand Prix spent more than S$560 million
($456 million) during race weekends over the past four years,
the government said.  The race has attracted more than 150,000 international
visitors to Singapore and over 360 million television viewers
worldwide since it was first held in the city state in 2008, the
Ministry of Trade and Industry said in a  statement  on its
website in response to a parliamentary question.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Chen in Singapore at 
